    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-12-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-12-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="477"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d477">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.51/914.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-12-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 18, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Government wishes to know whether or not this loan can be made against the
                    Public Works bonds now on deposit in the United States if, in your opinion,
                    interest will be saved thereby. The Government is in serious need of a part of
                    the loan at once.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Russell</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
